        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer589277483" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2689535713042928626">See my full review at Bitten By Books: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://bittenbybooks.com/63645/vampires-dont-sparkle-michael-west-editor/'>http://bittenbybooks.com/63645/vampir...</a><br/><br/>Vampires Don’t Sparkle! is a collection of stories that have one thing in common: they all highlight the good old-fashioned vampire. The vampires here are evil, wicked, and glory in all the blood they can. There are no creatures that regret their existence, pine after mortals, or limit themselves to subsist on animal blood. These are the vampires of old, the vampires that make us humans crave the daylight and fear the</span>
  <span id="freeText2689535713042928626" style="display:none">See my full review at Bitten By Books: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bittenbybooks.com/63645/vampires-dont-sparkle-michael-west-editor/">http://bittenbybooks.com/63645/vampir...</a><br /><br />Vampires Don’t Sparkle! is a collection of stories that have one thing in common: they all highlight the good old-fashioned vampire. The vampires here are evil, wicked, and glory in all the blood they can. There are no creatures that regret their existence, pine after mortals, or limit themselves to subsist on animal blood. These are the vampires of old, the vampires that make us humans crave the daylight and fear the darkness.</span>
